# Python and Flask Backend Rules

- Use Python 3.9+ typing where possible.
- Avoid wildcard imports.
- Format code cleanly, using clear and descriptive variable names.
- Ensure all Flask endpoints return standard JSON responses and use appropriate HTTP status codes.
- Exception handling should log errors without leaking sensitive data to the user.
- Add comprehensive docstrings to classes and complex functions.
